```python
def execute_command(system, tools):
    # Conduct experiments to determine if the neuron is selectively responsive to paper objects.
    # Challenge this by generating images of paper in various contexts and checking activation levels.
    prompt_list = [
        "a stack of colorful paper on a desk",
        "a newspaper lying on a park bench",
        "a child folding a paper airplane",
        "a pile of shredded paper",
        "an origami crane made of paper"
```

```python
def execute_command(system, tools):
    # To further challenge the selectivity for stacks of paper, particularly colorful ones, engage in controlled experiments:
    # Compare activations for a single sheet of paper versus stacks, and stacks of white paper versus stacks of colorful paper.
    prompt_list = [
        "a single white sheet of paper on a desk",
        "a stack of white paper on a desk",
        "a stack of colorful paper on a desk",
        "a stack of colorful paper in a recycling bin",
        "papers flying in the wind",
        "a book with white pages open on a table"  # Control image that contains paper but is not a loose paper or stack.
    ]
    
    editing_instructions_list = [
        "replace the single sheet of paper with a stack of white paper",
        "change the color of the stack of paper to multicolored",
        "replace the desk with a recycling bin",
        "make the paper heavier so they do not fly in the wind",
        "change the open book to a closed book"  # Control edit that maintains paper but changes the form.
    ]
    
    original_images, original_prompts = tools.text2image(prompt_list)
    edited_images, edited_prompts = tools.edit_images(original_prompts, editing_instructions_list)
    
    all_images = original_images + edited_images
    all_prompts = original_prompts + edited_prompts
    
    activation_list, activation_map_list = system.call_neuron(all_images)
    descriptions = tools.describe_images(activation_map_list, all_prompts)
    tools.save_experiment_log(activation_list, activation_map_list, all_prompts, descriptions)
```

```python
def execute_command(system, tools):
    # Conduct more targeted experiments to investigate the neuron's selectivity towards different aspects of paper.
    prompts = [
        "a single white sheet of paper on a desk",
        "a stack of white paper on a desk",
        "a stack of colorful paper on a desk"
    ]
    edits = [
        "replace the single sheet of paper with a stack of colorful paper",
        "change the colors of the stack of papers to all white",
        "place the stack of colorful paper in a recycling bin"
    ]
    
    # Generate original images based on prompts and then apply edits
    original_images, original_prompts = tools.text2image(prompts)
    edited_images, edited_prompts = tools.edit_images(prompts, edits)
    
    # Combine original and edited images into one list for neuron activation testing
    all_images = original_images + edited_images
    all_prompts = original_prompts + edited_prompts
    
    # Get neuron activation values and visually highlighted regions for each image
    activation_list, activation_map_list = system.call_neuron(all_images)
    
    # Get descriptions for the visually highlighted regions
    descriptions = tools.describe_images(activation_map_list, all_prompts)
    
    # Save experiment results
    tools.save_experiment_log(activation_list, activation_map_list, all_prompts, descriptions)
```

It appears the error is due to the improper unpacking of the results from `edit_images` which returns a tuple of lists, containing both the original and edited images, as well as their prompts. Let me revise the implementation to correctly handle the output:

[CODE]:
```python
def execute_command(system, tools):
    # Setup experiments to further investigate the neuron selectivity for paper
    prompts = [
        "a single white sheet of paper on a desk",
        "a stack of white paper on a desk",
        "a stack of colorful paper on a desk"
    ]
    
    edits = [
        "replace the white sheet of paper with a colorful one",
        "change the stack of white paper to colorful paper",
        "change the desk to a recycling bin"
    ]
    
    # Generate the original images for the base prompts
    original_images = tools.text2image(prompts)
    
    # Derive edited images based on the base images using the editing instructions
    edited_images, edited_prompts = tools.edit_images(prompts, edits)
    
    # Combine the original and edited images together, as well as their respective prompts
    all_images = original_images + edited_images
    all_prompts = prompts + edited_prompts
    
    # Test the activation of the neuron for all images
    activation_list, activation_map_list = system.call_neuron(all_images)
    
    # Describe the regions of high interest that activated the neuron
    descriptions = tools.describe_images(activation_map_list, all_prompts)
    
    # Save the results of the experiments in the log
    tools.save_experiment_log(activation_list, activation_map_list, all_prompts, descriptions)
```
